  "notes": "Nias (Li Niha), Barrier Islands off Sumatra, Indonesia. Latin orthography: six vowels including <ö> = /ɤ/; <ŵ> = /w/ while <w>/<v> spell the labiodental /v ~ ʋ/; <mb> and <ndr> are prenasalised/trilled-release units; <kh> = /x/; apostrophe = glottal stop. Every syllable is open (CV). Dialect differences (northern vs southern) affect several of these values; the northern standard is taken as the default.",
